As a significant contributor to EU energy consumption, traditional energy resource utilisation and carbon emissions, the building sector is subject to numerous policies and medium-term and long-term goals which seek to reduce the negative impact on climate change. The goals of the '20-20-20' target by 2020 is the set of three key objectives for:
* a 20% reduction in EU greenhouse gas emissions from 1999 levels;
* raising the share of EU energy produced from renewable sources by 20%;
* a 20% improvement in EU energy efficiency.

The main directives relevant to energy performance of the building stock are as follows:
* Directive 2010/31/EU on the energy performance of buildings (EPBD);
